==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amphisbæna
<hw>Am`phis*b⟦ae⟧"na</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <?/; <?/ on both ends + <?/ to go.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
fabled serpent with a head at each end, moving either way.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of harmless lizards,
serpentlike in form, without legs, and with both ends so much alike that
they appear to have a head at each, and ability to move either way. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <spn>Gordius aquaticus</spn>, or
<xex>hairworm</xex>, has been called an <gen>amphisbaena</gen>; but it
belongs among the worms.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amphisbaenoid</ent>⟦br⟧
